<br>
Name ONE Ragefire spawn that Vis Maior has come in and taken? NAME ONE. You can't, Our clerics for the majority have their epics and do NOT go to skyfire.<br>
<br>
Next How are we inconsiderate? We make deals with other guilds on the server for spawns. If you don't believe me, ask Lotus Cult. They'll be the first to tell you we work out deals with them.<br>
<br>
My posts on this thread was to point out that no matter what the list a few clerics make on this, it will not help. Simple of a fact that most the people on Quellious <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> DO NOT EVEN READ THIS FORUM</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and therefore will invoke the Play Nice Policy rules with GMs when it comes to a contested spawn. I am/was trying to point out a list will NOT work on Everquest due to the nature of people. And Yes a GM <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> WILL</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> award a spawn to anyone who is there FIRST with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> SUFFICIENT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> force. If you don't believe me, again Ask Lotus Cult, Wraith, Rel In Por, etc. <br>
<br>
Attacking me on this is in poor taste. I'm not even a cleric, but a individual that can see a MAJOR flaw in trying to get a list going here. There will <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> ALWAYS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be jerks on a server and theres nothing you can do about it. The way Verant has set up the Play Nice Policy on a Blue server severly benifits trolls/jerks/slimeballs/etc..<br>
<br>
The REASON why verant says &quot;SUFFICIENT FORCE&quot; is to stop guilds from sending one person to every spawn that that guild wants to hit and claim it camped. <br>
<br>
Is there a solution to Ragefire problems? In my opinion Yes.<br>
<br>
Simple put the Ragefire spawn on like the 4th or 5th island in the plane of air and make him a 24 hour spawn. In this way you will HAVE to have sufficient force to get to him, You will not get a contested spawn battle going (because yes, it takes keys to get to that island and it will be CLEAR on who should get him first). A side benifit would be that this zone would actually be used again. <br>
<br>
Other than something like I meantioned, the ONLY solution now is to have 12-16 of your friends camp ragefire with you. This will insure if he pops that you will get ragefire awarded to you.<br>
<br>
<br>
