 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/uwhytspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whytspirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Of the Nexus</span><br>  Posts: 310<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(5/31/02 2:50:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=654.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire Waiting List?</span><hr size=1> OK, time to add in my words again. A couple important things seem to have been missed by the naysayers. One was already pointed out. It is a way of handling the spawn IN game between clerics IN game. I too hope this list never hits the boards as something official. What we have here is NOT a cut and dried system, but a fellowship of clerics, their guilds and friends, all lending support to each other to accomplish a common goal. This started out simply when a cleric who wished to camp Ragefire after another cleric was done helped camp Rage, lent support simply for the first to call camp.<br>
<br>
This leads me to a second issue. In the case of a cleric not in &quot;the system&quot; camping Rage at the same time as someone on the &quot;list&quot;. Generally camp is announced every so often, so I would hope that this cleric who was interested in camping Ragefire would object, say &quot;umm, I am too&quot; and go work things out one way or the other. I am not going to spend a lot of time on this issue because most of the objections to the way its being handled and the inherent problems/issues aren't even clerics. <br>
<br>
This whole &quot;system&quot; is not anything formal. The &quot;list&quot; is exactly what was said, indicated interest (further proved by spending time out there as well). The reason this will work is because guild lines are not defined for this purpose necessarily. It is based on honor, respect and the willingness to help others. There is no alliance of guilds controlling this whole thing, contrary to what some of you may seem to think you know. <br>
<br>
Have we had a single spawn issue since this has been done? No, I don't think so. Why? Because folks are banding together for the greater good. Clerics and their friends are putting in the time. Gone are the days when a guild would sit their cleric alone in Skyfire to sit and wait for the human version to spawn and then have to rush into the zone, hopefully before somone else gets word. There are constantly people there, as well as extensive resources to forces that can be brought in quickly. <br>
<br>
Lastly, I am addressing the KS issue. Yes, it is possible for some unethical guild to come in with sufficient force and take the spawn away from the camping cleric. But with the number of people who are working to help that cleric, the call to arms can go out pretty quick to multiple guilds at once, so it would be a very impressive feat for the scumbags to accomplish.<br>
<br>
To those who are bringing in mention of the bad and nasty uber guilds. Please don't complicate this issue with that trash. There have been people from most of the guilds who have gotten a bad rap on these boards helping out. LC, ADD, Wraith, etc. What guild you are in as not as important as your willingness to support the clerics of our server. Again I ask people to head out there for a week, spend time and see for yourself how it is going. Send the cleric a tell of support. Wish them good luck. <br>
<br>
Don't assume everything that CAN go wrong WILL go wrong until you witness first hand what the real deal is.<br>
